<li id="cite_note-84"><b><a href="#cite_ref-84" title="">^</a></b> Computed; using in solar terms: 1.1 <i>M</i><sub>ʘ</sub> and 0.92<i>M</i><sub>ʘ</sub>, luminosities 1.57 and 0.51 <i>L</i>*/<i>L</i><sub>ʘ</sub>, Sun magnitude −26.73v), 11.2 to 35.6 AU orbit; The minimum luminosity adds planet's orbital radius to A-B distance (max) (conjunction). Max. luminosity subtracts the planet's orbital radius to A-B distance (min) (opposition).</li>
